This paper focuses on collaborative development workflows in open-source projects, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and software development (cs.SD) categories. The paper also discusses the structures of project repositories, which could fall under programming languages (cs.PL) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper analyzes the impact of workflows on project repositories, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves analyzing data.
